
1. Build your React app:
   ```
   npm run build
   ```

2. Create an S3 bucket:
   ```
   aws s3 mb s3://your-bucket-name
   ```


3. Configure the bucket for static website hosting:
   ```
   aws s3 website s3://your-bucket-name --index-document index.html --error-document index.html
   ```

bucket-policy.json
{
    "Version": "2012-10-17",
    "Statement": [
        {
            "Sid": "PublicReadGetObject",
            "Effect": "Allow",
            "Principal": "*",
            "Action": "s3:GetObject",
            "Resource": "arn:aws:s3:::your-bucket-name/*"
        }
    ]
}
4. Set bucket policy for public read access:
   ```
   aws s3api put-bucket-policy --bucket your-bucket-name --policy file://bucket-policy.json
   ```
   (Create a bucket-policy.json file with appropriate permissions)

5. Upload your React build to S3:
   ```
   aws s3 sync build/ s3://your-bucket-name
   ```

6. Create a CloudFront distribution:
   ```
   aws cloudfront create-distribution --origin-domain-name your-bucket-name.s3.amazonaws.com --default-root-object index.html
   ```

7. Update CloudFront distribution settings:
   ```
   aws cloudfront update-distribution --id YOUR_DISTRIBUTION_ID --default-root-object index.html
   ```

8. Create an SSL certificate in ACM (if using a custom domain):
   ```
   aws acm request-certificate --domain-name your-domain.com --validation-method DNS
   ```

9. Associate the SSL certificate with your CloudFront distribution:
   ```
   aws cloudfront update-distribution --id YOUR_DISTRIBUTION_ID --ssl-certificate-arn YOUR_ACM_CERTIFICATE_ARN
   ```

10. Update your domain's DNS settings to point to the CloudFront distribution.

Would you like me to explain or elaborate on any of these steps?
